   <h2> <b>Inaugural FIFA World Cup Tournament</b></h2>
       <p> <span>FIFA was founded in 1904, and the FIFA Men’s World Cup was held in 1930 for the first time. This tournament was organised by the FIFA president Jules Rimet. In this inaugural tournament, the FIFA World Cup was joined by 13 teams which were invited by the FIFA itself, including countries like Belgium, France, Romania and Hungary that were persuaded by Rimet. In addition, FIFA named Uruguay to become the first host country. Uruguay was also the first country to win the World Cup. 
</span></p>
    <p><span><b>Interesting fact:</b> According to Wikipedia, no european country committed to send a team to take part in this tournament until two months before the start of the match, one of the reasons being the trip to Uruguay was long and costly. 
</span></p><br />
    
    <h2><b>World Cup Before the Outbreak of World War II</b></h2>

  <p><span>FIFA had successfully held another two World Cup tournaments before the Outbreak of World War II in 1939. The second World Cup was held in the year 1934 and was hosted by Italy. This was the first World Cup  that included a qualification stage. A total of 16 teams from Europe, South America, Africa had qualified for this tournament. Italy, the host country, won this tournament. 
</span></p>

    <p><span><b>Interesting fact:</b> According to wikipedia, Egypt was the first African country to take part in this tournament. Uruguay boycotted the 1934 World Cup hence did not join this tournament.
</span></p><br />

    <p><span>The Third World Cup was held in France in 1938, a year before the outbreak of World War II. 15 countries competed in the finals, with Italy successfully retaining their title by beating Hungary in the final match. 
</span></p>

    <p><span><b>Interesting fact:</b> According to Wikipedia, Polish striker Ernest Willimowski became the first player to score four goals in a World Cup game and this record was not bettered until 1994 World Cup. 
</span></p><br />

    <h2><b>FIFA World Cup Cancelled Due to World War II</b></h2>
    <p><span>Following the outbreak of World War II, the FIFA World Cup had to be cancelled before the host country was selected. Due to the lack of financial and personnel resources, the FIFA World Cup could not resume immediately when the war ended in 1945. FIFA had intended to plan the next World Cup to be resumed in 1949, but no country wanted to host it. 
</span></p>

    <h2><b>FIFA World Cup After World War II, Before 21st Century</b></h2>

    <p><span>The forth FIFA Men’s World Cup resumed in 1950, held by Brazil. This was the first time that the British participated in this tournament. This tournament also witnessed the return of Uruguay. However, due to political reasons, countries like Hungary did not join the competition. Uruguay beat Brazil in this match, becoming the champions for the second time. 
</span></p>
   
    <p><span><b>Interesting fact:</b>According to Wikipedia, this tournament held the record of being the highest attendance of any sporting match. 
</span></p><br />
    <p><span>The 5th World Cup tournament held in Switzerland, in year 1954. This tournament has set a records, i.e., highest average goals per game, Hungary being the highest-scoring team, and most goals in a single match. This was the third time after game in 1938 and 1950, that the hosts did not win the World Cup trophy. 
</span></p>
    <p><span><b>Interesting fact:</b>Scotland joined the game for the first time. West Germany won the title. 
</span></p><br />

    <p><span>The 6th World Cup tournament was a significant game, as FIFA had ruled that qualification without playing was not allowed. Held in 1958 in Sweden, Brazil won the title for the first time.
</span></p>
    <p><span><b>Interesting fact:</b>World famous football player Pelé emerged in this tournament and scored 2 goals in the final. 
</span></p><br />

    <p><span>In the 1960s, there were 2 World Cup games hosted by Chile in 1962 and England in 1966 respectively. Brazil team had successfully retained the title, winnng their second World Cup in a row by beating Czechoslovakia (now known as Czech and Slovakia ). 
</span></p>

    <p><span><b>Interesting fact:</b>Although Pelé had shown his talent brightly in the previous game, he was absent in the 1962 World Cup final due to his injury in Brazil's second group match against Czechoslovakia at the beginning of the competition. 
</span></p><br />

    <p><span>The 1966 World Cup was the first ever tournament in FIFA World Cup history that had a mascot and official logo. Due to the discriminatory policy by FIFA that only one qualifying place was allocated to the regions of Asia, Oceania and Africa, African nations withdrew from the game. As a result, the eventual qualifiers from this zone, North Korea became the first Asian team to reach quarter-finals. 
</span></p>

    <p><span><b>Interesting fact: </b>World Cup trophy was stolen during the run-up match but was found 7 days later by a dog. South Africa was banned from playing in the game till 1992 when finally accepted again by FIFA.
</span></p><br />

    <h3><b>1970s & 1980s & 1990s</b></h3>

    <p><span>The 1970 World Cup was won by Brazil, making Brazil the first nation to win 3 World Cups. As a result, the Jules Rimet trophy was awarded to Brazil permanently for their achievement.

</span></p>

    <p><span><b>Interesting fact:</b>North Korea refused to meet and play with Israel, who for the first time grouped in the Asia/Oceania region. As such, North Korea was disqualified automatically. 
</span></p><br />

    <p><span>Political issues had been one of the issues that affected the FIFA World Cup ever since its inaugural game. The 1974 World Cup tournament was no exception. Soviet Union refused to travel to Chilean capital for political reason, making Chile won the intercontinental play-off. West germany won the title by beating Netherlands.</span></p>

    <p><span><b>Interesting fact:</b>A new trophy was created for this game.
</span></p><br />

    <p><span>The 1978 World Cup game was held in Argentina, and was the hardest game ever to qualify for. There were 95 countries competing for 14 places. Argentina won this game by beating Netherlands, making Netherlands the only nation in history to be the runners-up for two World Cup games in a row. 
</span></p>

    <p><span><b>Interesting fact:</b>Iran and Tunisia participated for the first time. Tunisia beat Mexico and became the first African country to win in a World Cup qualification game. 
</span></p><br />

    <p><span> World Cup tournaments were held in 1982 and 1986 in the 1980s, hosted by Spain and Mexico respectively.  The former game was won by Italy, while the latter was won by Argentina.
</span></p>

    <p><span><b>Interesting fact:</b>Italian captain Dino Zoff was the oldest player to win the World Cup in the 1982 game. 
</span></p><br />

    <p><span>In the 1990s, FIFA World Cup had became one of the most prestigous football competition in the world. In the 1998 World Cup tournament, a total attendance of nearly 3.6 million was recorded, making it the biggest in World Cup history. 
</span></p>

    <p><span><b>Interesting fact:</b>In 1998 World Cup second round match played by France and Paraguay, first golden goal was witnessed in World Cup history.  This tournament also witnessed the widest margin where Iran beat Maldives in qualification game by 17-0. 
</span></p><br />

